Generate typed API clients from the OpenAPI specification.

## What This Does

Reads `shared/api-contracts/openapi.yml` and generates typed client code for each platform using openapi-generator.

## Steps

1. Validate the OpenAPI spec: `task validate-api`
2. Run client generation: `task generate-clients`
3. Verify generated clients compile:
{% if "backend" in platforms %}   - `task backend:build`{% endif %}
{% if "web-user-app" in platforms %}   - `task web-user-app:build`{% endif %}
{% if "web-admin-portal" in platforms %}   - `task web-admin-portal:build`{% endif %}
{% if "mobile-android" in platforms %}   - `task mobile-android:build`{% endif %}
{% if "mobile-ios" in platforms %}   - `task mobile-ios:build` (Mac only){% endif %}

## Generated Output

{% if "web-user-app" in platforms or "web-admin-portal" in platforms %}- **TypeScript** (web-user-app + web-admin-portal): `web-user-app/src/lib/api/generated/`, `web-admin-portal/src/lib/api/generated/`{% endif %}
{% if "mobile-android" in platforms %}- **Kotlin** (Android): `mobile-android/app/src/main/kotlin/.../data/remote/generated/`{% endif %}
{% if "mobile-ios" in platforms %}- **Swift** (iOS): `mobile-ios/{{ project_slug }}/Data/Network/Generated/`{% endif %}

## When to Run

- After adding or modifying endpoints in `openapi.yml`
- After changing request/response schemas
- After running `/add-endpoint`
